# JavaScript Tutorial Notes

## What is JavaScript?

JavaScript (JS) is a programming language used to make websites interactive.

### Uses

* Frontend Development
* Backend Development (Node.js)
* Mobile Apps
* Desktop Apps
* Games
* Automation Scripts

---

# Variables

```js
let name = "Hamim";
const age = 25;
var city = "Dhaka";
```

### Difference

| Keyword | Reassign | Redeclare | Scope    |
| ------- | -------- | --------- | -------- |
| var     | âś…        | âś…         | Function |
| let     | âś…        | âťŚ         | Block    |
| const   | âťŚ        | âťŚ         | Block    |

---

# Data Types

## Primitive Types

```js
let name = "Hamim";     // String
let age = 25;           // Number
let isStudent = true;   // Boolean
let x = null;           // Null
let y;                  // Undefined
```

### Check Type

```js
console.log(typeof name);
```

---

# Operators

## Arithmetic

```js
+  // Addition
-  // Subtraction
*  // Multiplication
/  // Division
%  // Modulus
** // Power
```

Example:

```js
let result = 10 + 5;
```

---

# Conditionals

## if

```js
let age = 18;

if (age >= 18) {
  console.log("Adult");
}
```

## if else

```js
if (age >= 18) {
  console.log("Adult");
} else {
  console.log("Minor");
}
```

## Ternary Operator

```js
let message = age >= 18 ? "Adult" : "Minor";
```

---

# Loops

## For Loop

```js
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

## While Loop

```js
let i = 0;

while (i < 5) {
  console.log(i);
  i++;
}
```

---

# Functions

## Regular Function

```js
function greet(name) {
  return `Hello ${name}`;
}
```

## Arrow Function

```js
const greet = (name) => {
  return `Hello ${name}`;
};
```

Short Form:

```js
const greet = name => `Hello ${name}`;
```

---

# Arrays

```js
const fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Orange"];
```

### Access

```js
console.log(fruits[0]);
```

### Common Methods

```js
fruits.push("Mango");
fruits.pop();

fruits.shift();
fruits.unshift("Apple");
```

---

# Array Methods

## map()

```js
const nums = [1, 2, 3];

const doubled = nums.map(num => num * 2);
```

Result:

```js
[2, 4, 6]
```

---

## filter()

```js
const nums = [1, 2, 3, 4];

const even = nums.filter(num => num % 2 === 0);
```

Result:

```js
[2, 4]
```

---

## find()

```js
const users = [
  { id: 1, name: "Hamim" },
  { id: 2, name: "John" }
];

const user = users.find(u => u.id === 1);
```

---

# Objects

```js
const user = {
  name: "Hamim",
  age: 25,
  city: "Dhaka"
};
```

### Access Properties

```js
console.log(user.name);
console.log(user["age"]);
```

---

# Destructuring

```js
const user = {
  name: "Hamim",
  age: 25
};

const { name, age } = user;
```

---

# Template Literals

```js
const name = "Hamim";

console.log(`Hello ${name}`);
```

---

# Spread Operator

```js
const arr1 = [1, 2];
const arr2 = [...arr1, 3, 4];
```

Objects:

```js
const user = {
  name: "Hamim"
};

const updatedUser = {
  ...user,
  age: 25
};
```

---

# DOM Manipulation

## Select Element

```js
const title = document.getElementById("title");
```

```js
const title = document.querySelector(".title");
```

---

## Change Content

```js
title.textContent = "New Title";
```

---

## Change Style

```js
title.style.color = "red";
```

---

# Events

```js
const btn = document.querySelector("button");

btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
  alert("Clicked!");
});
```

---

# Async JavaScript

## setTimeout

```js
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("After 2 seconds");
}, 2000);
```

---

# Promises

```js
const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  resolve("Success");
});
```

```js
promise.then(data => {
  console.log(data);
});
```

---

# Async/Await

```js
async function getData() {
  const response = await fetch(url);
  const data = await response.json();

  return data;
}
```

---

# ES6 Features

### let & const

```js
let age = 25;
const country = "Bangladesh";
```

### Arrow Functions

```js
const sum = (a, b) => a + b;
```

### Template Literals

```js
`Hello ${name}`
```

### Destructuring

```js
const { name } = user;
```

### Spread Operator

```js
const newArr = [...arr];
```

---

# Error Handling

```js
try {
  let result = 10 / 0;
} catch (error) {
  console.log(error);
}
```

---

# Modules

## Export

```js
export const name = "Hamim";
```

## Import

```js
import { name } from "./user.js";
```

---

# Useful Methods

## String

```js
str.length
str.toUpperCase()
str.toLowerCase()
str.includes()
str.slice()
```

## Array

```js
push()
pop()
shift()
unshift()
map()
filter()
find()
reduce()
```

---

# Best Practices

âś… Use `const` by default

âś… Use meaningful variable names

âś… Keep functions small

âś… Write reusable code

âś… Use ES6+ features

âś… Handle errors properly

---

# Learning Path

1. Variables & Data Types
2. Operators
3. Conditions
4. Loops
5. Functions
6. Arrays
7. Objects
8. DOM
9. Events
10. Async JS
11. ES6+
12. Fetch API
13. Node.js
14. Express.js
15. React
16. TypeScript

---

## Final Example

```js
const users = [
  { name: "Hamim", age: 25 },
  { name: "John", age: 30 }
];

const adults = users
  .filter(user => user.age >= 18)
  .map(user => user.name);

console.log(adults);
```

Output:

```js
["Hamim", "John"]
```

